princeton_ansible.title: Remove 'update_cache: true' from roles unless explicit and useful

comments.body:
Related to #3206.

If we run the Update OS playbook regularly, that will update the cache on all machines, so we don't need to do it in the roles. This will make idempotency testing much easier.

Next failure is from the tests for the Drupal9 role, but it's an error in a handler marked `php`:
```
RUNNING HANDLER [php : restart apache] *****************************************
  fatal: [instance]: FAILED! => {"changed": false, "msg": "Output of config test was:\nenv: ‘apache2ctl’: No such file or directory\n"}
```

pulfalight.title: Show Online content icons on search results page

comments.body:
Per wireframe review meeting, this should be the full "[icon] has online content" tag as seen next to a collection title on a show page. The full tag should be used in all search results. It should be placed next to the container info. Both should be dropped down to a new line below the title.

The tag should say either "Has online content" or "Contains some online materials" depending on whether it directly or indirectly has online content.
